title: Jarryd Hayne explains fumbled punt return
text:
Jarryd Hayne explains fumbled punt return Last updated 11:25, October 6 2015 DOUG PENSINGER/GETTY IMAGES 
Jarryd Hayne says the San Francisco 49ers need to come together to end their losing streak. 
Jarryd Hayne has refused to point fingers at any of his San Francisco 49ers teammates, but says everyone needs to come together to break their losing streak. 
The 49ers were soundly beaten 17-3 by the Green Bay Packers yesterday on their home field - the team's third straight lopsided loss - with a fumbled punt return by one of many poor plays by San Francisco. 
It came in the second quarter when Hayne called for a fair catch, but there was a crash of bodies and his teammate LJ McCray accidentally took the Australian out.
